sentences.english: As to sacrifice, both he and Zeus delighted most in bulls.
sentences.chinese: 朱庇特和宙斯都最喜欢将公牛作为他们的供品。

sentences.english: Jupiter, to stop questions, replied that it was a fresh creation from the earth.
sentences.chinese: 朱庇特唯恐她再追问下去就答说这是大地的新造物。

sentences.english: Thunderbolt sped by Jove 's right hand sought out the height.
sentences.chinese: 朱庇特右手发射的霹雳总是寻找高处。

sentences.english: It does not clasp its hands and pray to Jupiter.
sentences.chinese: 它并不拱手向朱庇特大神祈祷。

sentences.english: Thunderbolt speed by jove's right hand seek out the height.
sentences.chinese: 朱庇特右手发射的霹雳总是寻找高处。

sentences.english: Jupiter shortened the spring, and divided the year into seasons.
sentences.chinese: 朱庇特缩短春天，把一年分为四季。

sentences.english: But it was only rather grudgingly that Jupiter granted mortals the use of fire.
sentences.chinese: 可是，朱庇特却是不大乐意允准人们用火的。

sentences.english: The guide showed us a colossal statue of Jupiter , in the Vatican.
sentences.chinese: 在梵蒂冈，向导领我们参观了一座朱庇特巨像。

sentences.english: Jupiter shortened the spring, and divided the year into four seasons.
sentences.chinese: 朱庇特缩短了春天，把一年分为四季。

sentences.english: An infant Bacchus or Jupiter is big with his future destiny.
sentences.chinese: 作为婴儿的巴库斯或朱庇特正孕育着其未来的命运。

sentences.english: Then he drove straight on to the little temple of Jupiter that overlooked the town.
sentences.chinese: 于是他就赶车直向俯视整个城镇的朱庇特小庙走去。
